<h2 id="arrest-in-japan">Arrest In Japan</h2>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Article 34.</strong> No person shall be arrested or detained without being at once informed of the charges against him or without the immediate privilege of counsel; nor shall he be detained without adequate cause; and upon demand of any person such cause must be immediately shown in open court in his presence and the presence of his counsel.<br />
<em>Translation of the Constitution of Japan</em></p>
</blockquote>
<ul>
<li>[ <a href="http://www.nichibenren.or.jp/en/legal/arrest_01.html" class="uri">http://www.nichibenren.or.jp/en/legal/arrest_01.html</a> JFBA advice ]</li>
<li>[ <a href="http://www.tlug.jp/ML/0610/msg00108.html" class="uri">http://www.tlug.jp/ML/0610/msg00108.html</a> US and British embassy advice ]</li>
<li>[ <a href="http://www.nichibenren.or.jp/en/legal/arrest_contact_list.html" class="uri">http://www.nichibenren.or.jp/en/legal/arrest_contact_list.html</a> duty Attorney contact numbers ]</li>
</ul>
